cut: separate lines into fields

sort: sort lines
Example: sort -t: -k3,3 -n /etc/group

uniq: print unique lines
Example: cut -d: -f7 /etc/passwd | sort | uniq -c
Output: 20 /bin/bash
        12 /bin/false

wc: count lines, words, and characters
-l --> newline count
-c --> byte count
-w --> word count

tee: copy input to two places

head and tail: read the beginning or end of a file
-n <NUM> --> first NUM files

grep: search text for a pattern
